00:52:21.939 --> 00:52:24.939
could I use to learn more about data stewardship?

00:52:24.939 --> 00:52:27.500
It doesn't need to be an ongoing or updated resource,

00:52:27.500 --> 00:52:29.340
but books would be fine too.

00:52:29.340 --> 00:52:30.699
Books would be fine too.

00:52:35.899 --> 00:52:39.820
Yeah, I think there is this data management book

00:52:39.820 --> 00:52:41.580
of knowledge called DMBOK.

00:52:43.179 --> 00:52:45.260
That's probably worth a read.

00:52:46.580 --> 00:52:48.540
I do think conversations like this

00:52:48.540 --> 00:52:50.820
and conversations with other people are very helpful.

00:52:50.820 --> 00:52:52.939
I don't know that this is like a,

00:52:52.939 --> 00:52:55.060
I don't think there's a lot of data stewardship books

00:52:55.060 --> 00:52:56.219
out there.

00:52:56.219 --> 00:52:59.100
I feel like this is kind of an emerging area.

00:53:00.100 --> 00:53:00.939
So I think a lot of the knowledge

00:53:00.939 --> 00:53:03.580
you'll get from your colleagues.

00:53:03.580 --> 00:53:05.459
But I'd love to see if people have stuff,

00:53:05.459 --> 00:53:06.899
maybe just drop it in the chat

00:53:06.899 --> 00:53:09.459
of where you've learned through this.

00:53:11.659 --> 00:53:13.100
Yeah, I would second that one.

00:53:13.100 --> 00:53:15.739
I also pasted on O'Reilly chapter up above

00:53:15.739 --> 00:53:17.659
that's just like a high level overview,

00:53:17.659 --> 00:53:21.139
quick fun read right before bed when I go to sleep.

00:53:22.100 --> 00:53:24.780
But I do also think one of the places

00:53:24.780 --> 00:53:26.340
you can look is ethics.

00:53:26.340 --> 00:53:28.540
So AI ethics and stuff like that

00:53:28.540 --> 00:53:30.219
is an exploding space right now.

00:53:30.219 --> 00:53:31.899
And there's a lot that actually ties back

00:53:31.899 --> 00:53:33.820
to the governance of the data.

00:53:33.820 --> 00:53:36.379
So to me, that's also a good kind of stream to follow.

00:53:36.379 --> 00:53:39.219
There's tons of different, really good resources on that.

00:53:41.100 --> 00:53:45.379
And even locally, we have coded bias kind of type of work.

00:53:45.379 --> 00:53:46.820
And that talks a lot about data

00:53:46.820 --> 00:53:47.820
and it can help you think about

00:53:47.820 --> 00:53:48.899
how to think about governance

00:53:48.899 --> 00:53:50.659
when you think about the bias it can create

00:53:50.659 --> 00:53:51.699
further down the pipeline.

00:53:51.699 --> 00:53:54.620
So I think that that might also be a helpful place

00:53:54.659 --> 00:53:56.179
when there isn't a lot of great resource

00:53:56.179 --> 00:53:57.179
at the ground level.

